{{Blurquote|image=Imageoceana4.png|quote-text= 

<div style="background-color:#FFFFFF; color: #485796; margin:1em; padding:2px 4px; border:4px solid #6495ED; border-radius: 12px">

<center>  <big><big><big>    <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.5em;">Description</span>  </big></big></big> </center> <hr style="border: none; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #6495ED, transparent);">

{{Blurimage|file=Imageoceana.png|caption=The first photo taken of Level 280.}}
<span style="font-size: 1.1em;"> 
'''Level 280,''' known as "''Blue Serenity''" resembles a complex marine observatory that expands across various rooms, corridors, and floors with a luminous and comforting aesthetic. The entire level has a technological structure and features various aquariums and minimalist decorations.

'''Level 280''' is illuminated by lights that vary between shades of blue and cyan. All the aquariums on this level are inhabited by various species of fish, some of which have already been seen in the frontrooms, and others that are still unknown.
The entire decorative structure within the level is designed simply and harmoniously, and it appears to aim for comfort and contrast between technology and ocean nature.

The level seems to be made in its primary structure of different materials such as quartz, polished marble, and various types of glass in its decorations. Its vast technological structure is perfectly designed, with no errors in its construction or any damage to its composition.

All of its technology, within the main zones, seems to have great emphasis on lights, which are present in a perfect and coordinated way on aquariums, floors, walls, and ceilings. Even with abundant electrical power over the lights and decorations, no single wire or even the slightest “error” can be found.

The atmosphere at '''Level 280''' is refreshing and features slightly low temperatures, remaining well-ventilated and soothing. These temperatures are not capable of causing any harm to individuals.

The surroundings of the level always remain silent, with the only element breaking the silence being soft music playing gently in various places throughout the complex.

{{Blurimage|file=Imageoceana3.png|caption=A photo taken from a hallway.}}
The level is structured of similar rooms and hallways that continue to repeat in a coordinated manner, presenting patterns that change slightly throughout the areas of '''Level 280'''. Patterns on the level can vary between long corridors, clusters of rooms, large halls, and short passages. Normally, '''Level 280''' is distributed in the form of large halls.

Walking on the level for a long time will cause the wanderer to get lost due to the variety of connections in corridors and rooms.
Although the level may seem like a vast technological maze, it is possible to find maps or graphical schematics that can help the wanderer find their way again.

Within the rooms on the level, various technological and aesthetic utensils used in normal laboratories can be found. When exploring any section, consumable food, and almond water can be found in high amounts, as well as various other supplies and rarely medicinal resources.

Any wanderer who enters '''Level 280''' will wake up from a deep sleep and find themselves lying on a bed, couch, or bench. The individual will not feel any negative aftereffects from the sleep, and on the contrary, will feel very energized, as if they had woken up from a good rest.

It is practically confirmed that two individuals cannot meet at the level, as no encounter between wanderers has been reported. This property should be accounted for due to the enormous size of the level and its significant expansion.


<center>  <big><big><big>    <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.5em;">The "''Wave of Peace''" Effect</span>  </big></big></big> </center> <hr style="border: none; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #6495ED, transparent);">

Any wanderer who enters '''Level 280''' will be under The "''Wave of Peace''" Effect.

Shortly after an individual enters '''Level 280''', they will feel like waking up from a deep sleep and will feel rested. After remaining for short periods of time within the level, the wanderer will begin to feel slightly sleepy.

The wanderer will continue to feel tired as time passes, and the desire to sleep will continue to take over their thoughts. The tiredness will continue to increase until the wanderer gives in and suddenly sleeps. This process usually takes 2 to 8 hours after entering the level.

Sleeping inside the level will cause the wanderer to leave '''Level 280''', and when they wake up, they will be on another level.
This effect will always occur and will be instantly nullified upon leaving the level.

The entire atmosphere and setting of the level help the wanderer feel more relaxed and fall asleep more quickly; however, various activities within the level can help the wanderer stay awake for longer.
Any individual under the ''"Wave of Peace"'' effect will remain calm, and for inexplicable reasons, wanderers who are under the effect will lose the ability to feel anger or sadness.

There are theories that '''level 280''' is a resting point for wanderers, like a true dream that materializes into comfort and happiness.
The origin of this effect is unknown, but it can indeed be considered something good due to its positive effects; however, one should avoid sleeping to remain at '''Level 280'''.


<center>  <big><big><big>    <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.5em;">Entities</span>  </big></big></big> </center> <hr style="border: none; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #6495ED, transparent);">

No encounters with any <u>documented</u> entities have occurred within '''Level 280'''.

However, the level has, in addition to certain types of unknown fish, a specific "entity".
{{Blurimage|file=Imageoceana5.png|width=200x200px|caption=A photo taken of an "AquaSystem".}}
This entity is known as '''"AquaSystem"''' and has the shape of an old computer. This computer resembles any other computer already seen in frontrooms, but it appears to use a different operating system than the ones known. 

Within this computer, various files, documents, maps of possible areas of the level, and even pixel-style games with an aquatic theme can be found. 

Numerous folders containing codes and unknown archives can also be found; it is still unknown what they mean or what is inside most of the archives, as passwords are required to access them.
These computers do not appear to be connected to any kind of network or Wi-Fi.

These entities can not only be found in the form of old computers, they can also be found in the form of technological computers or notebooks. They all feature the same unknown operating system that goes by the name '''"AquaSystem"'''. Many of these entities can be found around '''Level 280''' in groups, or individually. 

