<center>  <big><big><big>    <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.5em;">Colonies and Outposts</span>  </big></big></big> </center> <hr style="border: none; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #6495ED, transparent);">

Due to the vast structure and expansion of '''Level 280''', it is not possible for individuals to meet.
In this way, it is impossible to establish any colonies or outposts inside the level.


<center>  <big><big><big>    <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.5em;">Entrances and Exits</span>  </big></big></big> </center> <hr style="border: none; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #6495ED, transparent);">

<center> <big><big><big> <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.2em;"><span style="color:#4169E1;">Entrances</span></span> </big></big></big> </center> 

•Sleeping deeply at any level has a minimal chance to make one wake up here.

•No-clipping at any water-themed level has an extremely low chance to make one wake up here.

•Having a 50-99 karma rating in [[Level 995]] has a chance of taking you here.

<center> <big><big><big> <span style="font-family:Akaya Telivigala; font-size: 1.2em;"><span style="color:#4169E1;">Exits</span></span> </big></big></big> </center> 

•Sleeping will take one to a random water-themed level.

*Either sleeping or wandering far enough in Level 280 leads to [[Level 512]];

•Walking through futuristic areas illuminated by white lights can take one to [[Level 15]].

•No-clipping through an aquarium can take one to [[level 7]] or [[Level 37]].

•Opening a file named "Wakeup" in a '''"AquaSystem"''' will take one to a random water-themed level.
